1�Not anyone can go in there--the Korroloka Tunnel has been closed for over a hundred years.
1�Not anyone can go in there--the Korroloka Tunnel has been closed for over a hundred years.
1�However, permission to pass has been granted to adventurers who have proven their worth.Adventurers such as yourself.
1�Would you like to enter?Let me through.Not this time.
1�Would you like to enter?Let me through.Not this time.
1�Wh-what, you got a problem?There's plenty of work up here. Why should I go deeper into those creepy mines!?
1�I wish I could change jobs as easily as you adventurers.Being crammed in this place with all these Galka makes my skin crawl.
1�Yeah, I'm a foreman, too, but you want Makarim.She's waiting for you with her report. You can find her deeper in the mines.
1�Oi, an adventurer! Whatcha wasting time up here for? Go down there and rid us of some pesky monsters, why don'tcha?
1�Shipments of mythril used to be ferried to this dock from the Palborough Mines, but it's been closed off since the Quadav took Palborough.
1�So you heard the details of the incident on Ore Street?
1�That child who calls himself the Talekeeper... We need to find out if what he says is true, but they're still hammering out the details of the plan upstairs.
1�If we assume from the beginning that he's a fake, it could cast a shadow on our pride. That's probably what's keeping the officials from making a quick decision.
1�Sir Iron Eater! So, we have received clearance to send adventurers on this expedition?
1�If you happen to find 6????, take it to Tall Mountain, a guard in the off-limits area in the Mines District.
1�If you happen to find 6????, take it to Tall Mountain, a guard in the off-limits area in the Mines District.
1�Ah, you are the one we sent to Zepwell Island. I'm surprised you were so successful in revealing the true colors of that imposter.
1�In any case, I just received a message stating that Sir Iron Eater is currently on his way here.
1�I wish there were not, but we cannot allow civilians into such a dangerous place.
1�When you find proof of Werei's journey, bring it here. I'll be waiting for you.
1�Well, it looks like Werei left a message on this piece of wood. This is an important find in our investigation.
1�Good. Now for--what? Is anything wrong, Foreman Makarim?
1�What!?
1�Oh, you don't wanna waste time talking to us miners, do you?Why don't you be nice and squash us some monsters instead!
1�As always, we Galka do all the work, while Humes just watch.
1�We reopened these Zeruhn Mines here after the Quadav took Palborough.
1�Work, work, work...
1�We shouldn't have to oversee the Galka at all.I wish our peoples would forget our differences and work together...
1�Ah, you must be the courier. I've been expecting you.My report is ready.
1�Be careful on your way out.Remember, you should give my report to Naji, one of the Mythril Musketeers on post at the President's Office.
1�Come quick! The Galka from the Mines District have forced their way up to the entrance of the mine!
1�What, is it so strange to see a Hume doing some honest work?Well, I wouldn't have to, if that foreman wasn't always watching...
1�We used to get more ore out of these mines in the old days...
1�Why are you looking at me that way?Have you never seen a dark knight before?
1�You say Gumbah told you about me? That child is always crossing the line. It's unfortunate what happened to Werei, but I see Volker has not changed.
1�I had thought I might visit the Mines District...but if they are still there, I should probably not.
1�And why is it that you have sought me out? You seek training to become a dark knight, perhaps? Yes...I sense you have already felled many enemies...
1�But the way of the dark knight is not one to be taken lightly. It is a hopeless road, where anger and sorrow are your only companions.
1�But if you still wish to become one, then take this sword. Let it feed on your bloodlust and the blood of your enemies.
1�I must go. I have some business to attend to in Beadeaux, the Quadav stronghold. Sate that sword's hunger, and we will meet again...
1�I wish I was an adventurer like you, free to go wherever I like.
1�Every day, all I do is dig tunnels in this dank place, and when I go home, my wife bosses me around...
1�What's this? A note from my wife?
1�Hah! What does she think I do all day--play dice with Goblins!?
1�Just tell her I got her message, and to not bother me again.
1�What's this? A note from my wife?
1�You've read this, haven't you? See what she wants me to do? The groceries! What does she think I do all day, play dice with Goblins!?
1�Say, since you've read this note, can you go and get her  $???? instead of me?
1�I can't run around doing everything she tells me to--I have my dignity to uphold!

1�I will take responsibility for the adventurer's actions. Give ?[him/her] ?[his/her] orders.
1�We have always had such clearance. Yet none of us knew the task to give the adventurers...until now.
1�I want you to journey to the Altepa Desert and see if the so-called Talekeeper's story is true.
1�He is saying that he found 6???? near the Revelation Rock himself.
1�If it is real, there is no way a normal child could have gotten his hands on it. It may prove that he is indeed the true Talekeeper.
1�And if it is a fake, I want you to try to find 6????. This will more than likely be a difficult task.
1�This is a very strange situation for me, but I would like to know the truth. That is all. Good luck on your mission.
1�I'm sorry about giving you all this extra work, Drake Fang. So, have there been any more complaints about not opening the Korroloka Tunnel to the public?
1�People assume that locked doors always hide secrets, and there is little we can do to change that perception. We need to get that investigation report finished as soon as possible...
1�I was supposed to accompany the expeditionary trip to Zepwell Island myself, but I was worried about the happenings in the Mines District.
1�It's almost like all the residents' discontent and hatred have come to a dangerous boil...
1�And there is one other thing...something that Zeid said. It was like he was predicting the arrival of the true Talekeeper.
1�In any case, I'm leaving this next expedition to you. This is not official, but we have heard that Werei had set off for the Kuftal Tunnel.
1�We want you to go to the tunnel, find proof that he had been there, and bring it back to Drake Fang.
l.�I keep tellin' the guard to let me into the Korroloka Tunnel, but he says it's off-limits to guys like me. I'm sure that a little bit of monetary persuasion'd change his mind.
1�That's a sacred place for us Galka. I can't believe that he'd let a Hume with a little cash pass, but force me to stay on this side.

1�I travel all over the world and hear lots of differererent stories. I even hear your stories. I can tell you one, if you want.
